File: SA's death toll is 22,067 with recoveries at 744,298. AFP/Jens Schlueter JOHANNESBURG - The Health Department reported 4,645 more COVID-19 infections in South Africa. READ: WHO warns virus crisis not over as vaccine rollout approaches Over 100 more deaths were also reported, with most having occurred in the Eastern Cape. The total number of confirmed COVID-19 cases is now 810,449. SA's death toll is 22,067 with recoveries at 744,298.